# This is the statistics module which has a lot of different functions that can be used to calculate different things. In this case we are using the mean function to calculate the average of the numbers in the list. The mean function takes a list of numbers as an argument and returns the average of those numbers. In this case, the average of 100, 90, 100, and 70 is 90.
import statistics

print(statistics.mean([100,90,100,70]))